  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For microimages far away from the source position, β, these terms become very large.",
    "Consequently, the sum of the deflections due to the microlenses (see Eq.",
    "(1)) must also become very large.",
    "Because point mass deflections are proportional to 1/|θθ i |, the location of the microimage is required to be very close to some microlens so that a single term in the sum dominates.",
    "It can be shown that the magnifications of these far away micro-images behave as μ ∝ |θ | -4 (Paczynski 1986; Schneider and Weiss 1987), and they are therefore faint saddle points."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "It can be shown that the magnifications of these far away micro-images behave as μ ∝ |θ | -4 (Paczynski 1986; Schneider and Weiss 1987), and they are therefore faint saddle points."
  ]
